1
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:41,020
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:43,979
[Episode 35]

3
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:49,759
This is our first cooperation.

4
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:52,620
But I don't want it to be the last time.

5
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:54,310
I hope we can create more

6
00:01:54,310 --> 00:01:55,120
next time.

7
00:01:55,509 --> 00:01:56,970
More surprises together.

8
00:01:57,229 --> 00:01:58,120
Can we?

9
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:02,250
Yes.

10
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:03,600
Thank you.

11
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:38,290
Come on, cheers.

12
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,070
You guys talk. I'll go over there.

13
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:11,500
Congratulations, Kevin.

14
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,150
I'm sorry

15
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:20,079
for making you ride
the roller coaster with me again.

16
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:21,800
If the boss himself,

17
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,560
who almost flew off
the roller coaster, doesn't mind,

18
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,870
why should I mind?

19
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:28,160
Although I was singing
a different tune the whole time,

20
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:29,440
it turns out

21
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:31,060
this adventure was worth it.

22
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,760
I meant no harm.

23
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,010
Maybe I'm just old.

24
00:03:35,970 --> 00:03:38,350
Why are you suddenly getting sentimental?

25
00:03:38,350 --> 00:03:39,829
No matter what, Cindy,

26
00:03:39,850 --> 00:03:41,300
you'll always be my CFO.

27
00:03:41,329 --> 00:03:42,810
That will never change.

28
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:43,829
You know what?

29
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:45,840
I used to think

30
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:48,400
that was the most beautiful
love confession.

31
00:03:48,980 --> 00:03:49,579
Really.

32
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:52,370
I actually gave up marrying you

33
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,329
to be your CFO in your company

34
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,470
to secure a longer

35
00:03:55,490 --> 00:03:57,900
and more stable relationship.

36
00:03:58,760 --> 00:03:59,880
Tell me,

37
00:04:00,270 --> 00:04:02,220
do you think I'm ridiculous

38
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,300
and unreasonable?

39
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,310
If you suddenly confess your love,

40
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:07,240
I wouldn't know what to do.

41
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,160
What are you so proud of?

42
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:14,430
I'm just sighing
about my past childishness.

43
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,920
I have many suitors now too.

44
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:18,450
I know. I know.

45
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:22,710
It's just that when I saw

46
00:04:22,710 --> 00:04:24,670
the way you looked at Xu Miyu,

47
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:27,320
I had a bystander's perspective

48
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:29,400
and clearly saw what love looks like.

49
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,460
So tomorrow,

50
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:33,010
are you really not going back with us?

51
00:04:33,830 --> 00:04:34,920
I want to stay here for a while

52
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:35,800
to keep my father company.

53
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,560
You think I don't know

54
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,240
you stayed for Ms. Xu?

55
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,310
I wish you happiness soon.

56
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,520
You too.

57
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:50,860
I'm leaving.

58
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:04,940
Thanks to you this time.

59
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:05,650
Miyu.

60
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:06,940
We'll be leaving then.

61
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:11,260
Let's dance.

62
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,160
It's fine, come on.

63
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,920
Did you and Ji Feng

64
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:57,750
have a falling out

65
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:59,480
because of the art exhibition?

66
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:03,850
Is it that obvious?

67
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:06,390
Your expression just now

68
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:07,870
was like David Jagger's

69
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:09,430
melancholy Catherine.

70
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:15,920
You said earlier

71
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,380
you didn't dare to
start a certain painting.

72
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:21,000
You were talking about Ji Feng, right?

73
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,890
But it felt wrong to start.

74
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:29,720
If it were me,

75
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:32,150
I would protect you immediately,

76
00:06:33,070 --> 00:06:35,070
no matter what kind of enemy we face.

77
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,330
I mean it.

78
00:06:39,050 --> 00:06:41,159
I've also experienced
failed relationships.

79
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:43,040
My biggest realization now is that

80
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,370
a good relationship

81
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,680
isn't about how useful
the other person is,

82
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,340
but about unconditional
trust and protection.

83
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:52,090
What do you think?

